  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite being a recent publication in 2021, \"Making Home(s) in Displacement\" has yet to garner citations or significant online discourse. However, its focus on sustainability and policy relevance, alongside commercial availability through platforms like Amazon and Goodreads, suggests an emerging interest that may develop over time.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Making Home(s) in Displacement\" was published by Leuven University Press in 2021 and addresses the critical intersections of home and displacement. While this work has not yet received citations or substantial online engagement on platforms such as Reddit or Wikipedia, it is available for commercial purchase, indicating a potential for broader reach and impact in the coming years.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book demonstrates a commitment to addressing pressing issues related to sustainability and policy, which is reflected in its inferred strength in this domain. Specifically, the work is associated with one Sustainable Development Goal, further underscoring its relevance to contemporary societal challenges.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Although community discourse surrounding the book appears minimal at this stage, this lack of attention may change as readers and scholars begin to engage more deeply with its themes. The absence of mentions in social and community platforms suggests an opportunity for future discussions that could enhance its visibility and influence within both academic and public spheres.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, while \"Making Home(s) in Displacement\" currently lacks widespread recognition or citation metrics, its potential relevance to sustainability issues highlights an important area for future exploration. As conversations around displacement continue to evolve, this work may serve as a valuable resource for both scholars and practitioners interested in navigating these complex topics.</p>",
